# MOC Governance

Apply these conventions inside `Projects/<Project Name>/` subfolders.

## Decisions (`decisions/`)

- One ADR per file. Filename: `adr-YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`.
- Required sections: TL;DR, Context, Options, Decision, Consequences, Alternatives Considered, Related ADRs, References.
- `status`: `proposed | accepted | superseded | deprecated`.
- Superseding ADRs must link the ADR they replace and vice versa.
- Link every ADR from `MOC.md` under `Open Decisions` or `Quick Links`.

## Changelog (`changelog/`)

- One entry per file. Filename: `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`.
- Required sections: TL;DR, Change, Reason, Impact, Links.
- Keep factual; no narrative.
- Link the latest 3-5 entries from `MOC.md` under `Recent Changes`.

## Backlog (`backlog/`)

- One item per file. Filename: `<slug>.md`.
- Required sections: TL;DR, Description, Acceptance Criteria, Priority, Dependencies, Links.
- `status`: `draft | ready | in-progress | blocked | done | dropped`.
- `priority`: `p0 | p1 | p2 | p3`.
- Active top items linked from `MOC.md` under `Active Backlog`.

## Runbooks (`runbooks/`)

- Required sections: TL;DR, Scope, Preconditions, Procedure, Rollback, Validation, Related Incidents.
- Linked from `MOC.md` when operationally relevant.

## Meetings (`meetings/`)

- Filename: `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`.
- Link decisions or backlog items created from the meeting.

## Archive lifecycle

- On project completion, move project-only inactive notes to `Projects/<Project Name>/archive/`.
- Promote reusable artifacts to `Resources/` and update links in `MOC.md`.
- Do not delete notes; archive them.

## Agent behavior

- When creating governance notes, always include the frontmatter and sections above.
- Keep IDs and filenames aligned (`id` in frontmatter matches the filename slug).
